es in SFR estimates based\non Halpha can be reduced to a factor of only 2-3, even if the Halpha line is\nblended with the adjacent [NII] lines. Without Halpha, however, the SFR is\ndifficult to estimate from the [OII], Hbeta, and [OIII] lines. (abridged)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 8 Jan 2001 10:22:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-24"}
