{"id":"math/0101058","submitter":"Franc Forstneric","authors":"Miran Cerne and Franc Forstneric","title":"Embedding some bordered Riemann surfaces in the affine plane","comments":null,"journal-ref":"Math. Res. Lett., 9 (2002), 683--696","doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.CV","license":null,"abstract":"  We study the existence of proper holomorphic embeddings of bordered Riemann\nsurfaces into the complex plane C^2. Denote by M(R) the moduli space consisting\nof all equivalence classes of complex structures J on a given smooth oriented\nbordered surface R. We introduce a class F(R) in M(R)with the following\nproperties: (1) F(R) is nonempty and open (in a natural topology on M(R)); (2)\nThe interior of any Riemann surface (R,J) in the class F(R) admits a proper\nholomorphic embedding in C^2; (3) If R is a finitely connected planar domain\nthen F(R)=M(R); (4) Each hyperelliptic bordered Riemann surface (R,J) belongs\nto the class F(R) and hence admits a proper holomorphic embedding in C^2. Part\n(3) above is equivalent to the theorem of Globevnik and Stensones (Holomorphic\nembeddings of planar domains into C^2, Math. Ann. 303, 579-597, 1995). Our\napproach builds upon the earlier work of Cerne and Globevnik (On holomorphic\nembedding of planar domains into C^2, J. d'Analyse Math. 8, 269-282, 2000).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 8 Jan 2001 08:37:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 16 May 2003 11:54:27 GMT"}],"update_date":"2007-05-23"}
